<item>
            <title>[LU-16563] LNet: use discovery ni status to set peer ni availability </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16563</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently when MR peer is being discovered, it replies with the list of its NIs and their status.&#160; Even if NI is &quot;down&quot; due to a &quot;fatal&quot; condition like locally detected &quot;link down&quot;, it is listed with &quot;UP&quot; status in the reply, so the recipient can find out that the NI is not reachable only by trying to communicate to it and failing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, to avoid unnecessary delay in this scenario, NI status can be tracked such that locally recognized &quot;down&quot; state is available to any discovering peer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
